{
    "name": "Horn Caterpillar",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Unlike normal caterpillars, voracious giant horn caterpillars don\u2019t pupate into butterflies. Instead, they remain in their worm-like forms for their entire life cycle, growing between each molt until they eventually reach the size of large dogs.<br/><br/>Horn caterpillars feed on the hooves and horns of dead ungulates, which they usually scavenge from corpses. Their sharp mandibles allow them to effortlessly shear through tendon and bone."
        }
    ],
